## Checklist
Cross-cutting secure-default gates. Per-topic and per-infrastructure
overlays live as file-backed references under
`references/` and are linked from the relevant rows below.

- [ ] **Input** — untrusted input is rejected or typed at the boundary
      before reaching business logic.
      Overlay: `references/injection.md`.
- [ ] **Authentication** — framework-standard primitives; no
      hand-rolled crypto or session handling.
      Overlay: `references/authentication.md`.
- [ ] **Authorization** — re-checked at the resource boundary, not
      inferred from the caller.
      Overlay: `references/authorization.md`.
- [ ] **Output encoding** — user-supplied data is encoded for its sink
      (HTML, SQL, shell, template) before interpolation.
      Overlays: `references/xss.md`, `references/injection.md`.
- [ ] **Server-side requests** — no unchecked user-controlled URLs,
      metadata endpoints, or internal network targets.
      Overlay: `references/ssrf.md`.
- [ ] **Secrets** — not logged, serialized, or returned in error
      payloads; envelope/KMS-backed at rest.
- [ ] **Error paths** — fail closed; unexpected states do not expose
      privileged operations or internal surface area.
- [ ] **Dependency boundary** — third-party calls cite the library's
      documented safe-usage pattern; pinned versions only.
- [ ] **Insecure defaults** — permissive CORS, unverified TLS, weak
      hashing, `eval`/shell composition: absent or explicitly justified.

## Targeted overlays
When the change touches the following surface, also hydrate the
overlay for that surface. Overlays do not replace the cross-cutting
checklist; they extend it.

| surface | overlay |
